Abilities & Powers

Unparalleled Strength: As his name implies, The Juggernaut is mercilessly destructive and unstoppable. His strength is so great it's its own defense. He possesses seemingly limitless physical power, capable of effortlessly defeating powerful monsters and targets with a single casual punch. His punches are so powerful that many monsters simply explode when struck—though he often holds back to prolong the fight.
Unparalleled Speed and Reflexes: Capable of creating custom weapons, armor, houses, and giant clothing in the blink of an eye. His strength also makes him insanely fast—fast enough to perform an infinite mass punch, delivered at such high speed (approaching the speed of light) that its mass, and thus momentum, effectively becomes infinite. He can also perform bullet time, giving him the precision to pinpoint opponents or body parts.
Superhuman Stamina and Endurance: The Juggernaut only sleeps to pass time, like meditation. He has gone several days and nights without rest, survived the deepest, darkest depths of the ocean while holding his breath, endured the vacuum of space and re-entry into Earth's atmosphere with half a brain and no heart, and survived Cthulhu's Oneiropathy.
Healing Factor: He has an incredible regenerative ability, making him nearly impossible to kill. He can regrow skin, muscle, bones—even entire organs. His healing factor also slows his aging process: the older he gets, the slower he ages. If decapitated, his severed parts retain cognizance and can be reattached. He is immune to diseases and toxins, including zombie viruses.
Pain Suppression: It’s unclear whether years of battle have made him indifferent to pain or if he literally cannot feel it. Regardless, The Juggernaut responds little—if at all—to injuries. At most, he may freeze momentarily, possibly as an intimidation tactic to lull opponents into a false sense of security. When stepped on by a giantess, he felt only frustration as he was forced into the ground.
